The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Raymond plans to invest Rs 197 cr

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, March 10: Raymond Ltd will invest Rs 197 crore to expand capacity at its integrated fabric manufacturing facility at Vapi in Gujarat.

 According to the plan, the company will expand capacity for worsted or polyester suiting fabrics by 3 million metres per annum, resulting in a total capacity of 31 million metres per annum.

 This would be an integrated facility starting from spinning to finishing of fabric and is expected to go on stream in April next year. 

 The company had started the first phase of expansion last year, which is expected to begin commercial production soon. After this expansion, the company will have a total capacity of 31 million metres per annum of worsted suiting. 

 The outlook for the textile business continues to be buoyant and to keep up with that, the company is putting up advanced manufacturing capacities and forging partnerships with internationally well reputed premium players, Raymond chairman Gautam Hari Singhania said.

 The textiles division of the company had recorded a revenue of Rs 612 crore for the nine months ended December 2005, a growth of 12 per cent over the corresponding period last fiscal. The suits and trousers manufacturing facility set up by the company as part of its strategy to be a One- Stop Shop is already operational. 




